LEADERSHIP compiles six things about the newly appointed Chief of Army Staff, Major General Farouk Yahaya. Below are the things that may be hitherto unknown about the new COAS: Major General Farouk Yahaya is of Regular Course 37 of the Nigerian Defence Academy (NDA). He hails from Sokoto State. Until his appointment, he was the Theatre Commander, Operation Hadin Kai, formerly known as Operation Lafiya Dole in the North-East. Yahaya took over from Maj-Gen. Olusegun Adeniyi, who was redeployed to the Nigerian Army Resource Centre as Senior Research Fellow. He was also formerly General Officer Commanding Officer of the 1 Division of the Nigerian Army, Kaduna. Gen. Yahaya was also the Commander of 4 Brigade Headquarters of the Nigerian Army.